15
00:01:52.069 --> 00:01:54.865
All right. everybody off!

16
00:01:55.031 --> 00:01:56.867
Whoo!

17
00:02:00.578 --> 00:02:02.804
Gotta call this in.

18
00:02:02.929 --> 00:02:04.102
Miss!

19
00:02:15.692 --> 00:02:19.087
Dying on a streetcar
while dancing to <i>Y.M.C.A.</i>

20
00:02:19.212 --> 00:02:20.372
What do you think?

21
00:02:20.497 --> 00:02:22.357
Sounds like a crappy way to go.

22
00:02:22.482 --> 00:02:25.160
Hey. Body I.D.'d as Serena Dunbrook.

23
00:02:25.285 --> 00:02:27.696
34. lives in the pearl.

24
00:02:27.821 --> 00:02:28.881
Probably on her way to work.

25
00:02:29.006 --> 00:02:30.132
Which is the swank law firm

26
00:02:30.257 --> 00:02:31.750
of Berman. Rautbort. and Associates.

27
00:02:31.875 --> 00:02:34.321
Wallet biopsy on her purse?

28
00:02:35.571 --> 00:02:37.032
This is our victim.

29
00:02:37.831 --> 00:02:39.874
That's what she used to look like.

30
00:02:49.297 --> 00:02:58.303
<font color="#3399FF">Sync and correction by Mlmlte</font>
<font color="#3399FF">www.addic7ed.com</font>

31
00:03:00.311 --> 00:03:02.690
It's unofficial but Kick Squad's
thinking anaphylactic shock.

32
00:03:02.815 --> 00:03:04.901
That could happen
from one little bee sting?

33
00:03:05.026 --> 00:03:06.268
We need to get the M.E.
On her medical records.

34
00:03:06.393 --> 00:03:07.646
See if she was allergic to anything.

35
00:03:07.812 --> 00:03:09.564
Ask me. this is a waste of your time.

36
00:03:09.730 --> 00:03:11.691
We don't know
if this was an accident yet.

37
00:03:11.857 --> 00:03:13.360
Must've been a killer bee. huh?

38
00:03:13.526 --> 00:03:15.044
There was a swarm that attacked a dog

39
00:03:15.169 --> 00:03:16.530
in Cathedral Park last week.

40
00:03:16.696 --> 00:03:19.749
Okay. come on.
20 bucks says no foul play.

41
00:03:19.874 --> 00:03:20.750
Who's in?

42
00:03:20.875 --> 00:03:21.743
Me.

43
00:03:21.909 --> 00:03:23.355
Pay up.

44
00:03:25.538 --> 00:03:27.541
Looks like a puncture wound.

45
00:03:29.714 --> 00:03:30.977
Maybe a needle.

46
00:03:31.102 --> 00:03:32.452
More like a nail.

47
00:03:34.021 --> 00:03:35.507
Time to get Harper out of bed.

48
00:03:35.673 --> 00:03:37.767
Ooh. lucky you.

49
00:03:37.892 --> 00:03:39.719
Bet your gal's
wearing something sexy.

50
00:03:41.069 --> 00:03:42.119
Here it is.

51
00:03:43.097 --> 00:03:45.475
Cause of death: Anaphylactic shock.

52
00:03:45.641 --> 00:03:47.519
Mode: Apitoxin.

53
00:03:47.685 --> 00:03:49.396
As in bee venom.

54
00:03:49.562 --> 00:03:50.522
Gold star.

55
00:03:50.688 --> 00:03:53.191
Phylum Anthropoda.
Class insecta.

56
00:03:53.357 --> 00:03:55.026
I sent a sample to a local apiarist

57
00:03:55.192 --> 00:03:56.611
for further analysis.

58
00:03:56.777 --> 00:03:59.155
That's a beekeeper.
I can play this game too.

59
00:03:59.321 --> 00:04:00.907
Now. let's pretend
that it wasn't a bee sting.

60
00:04:01.073 --> 00:04:03.493
Oh.
Going for the extra credit.

61
00:04:03.659 --> 00:04:06.371
Well. it's definitely
a puncture wound.

62
00:04:06.537 --> 00:04:08.915
But I can't tell you what made it.

63
00:04:09.081 --> 00:04:13.295
I've never seen
a needle gauge this big.

64
00:04:13.461 --> 00:04:15.213
So was she allergic to apitoxin?

65
00:04:15.379 --> 00:04:19.582
No. But medical records
never kept anyone from dying.

66
00:04:19.707 --> 00:04:24.347
I found close to 50 milligrams
of apitoxin in her system.

67
00:04:24.513 --> 00:04:27.225
F.Y.I.. a bee sting carries
about .1 milligram.

68
00:04:27.391 --> 00:04:30.437
That would make it a bee
the size of LeBron James.

69
00:04:30.603 --> 00:04:32.063
More like the big three combined.

70
00:04:32.229 --> 00:04:33.398
Okay. sports fans.

71
00:04:33.564 --> 00:04:35.892
So Serena Dunbrook
gets on a Portland streetcar.

72
00:04:36.017 --> 00:04:37.777
people erupt
into spontaneous dance...

73
00:04:37.943 --> 00:04:39.979
And our opportunistic killer
takes advantage of the chaos.

74
00:04:40.104 --> 00:04:41.448
injects her with bee venom...

75
00:04:41.614 --> 00:04:42.782
Weird. but possible.

76
00:04:42.948 --> 00:04:44.734
And definitely...

77
00:04:44.859 --> 00:04:49.830
Definitely a homicide.

78
00:04:52.600 --> 00:04:55.003
7:14 A.M.. there's your victim.

79
00:04:55.169 --> 00:04:57.130
Got her.
Move past this.

80
00:04:57.296 --> 00:04:59.648
All right.
Anything...

81
00:04:59.773 --> 00:05:02.719
Anyone eying her wrong.
reaching for anything?

82
00:05:02.885 --> 00:05:06.181
Okay. now slow it back down.

83
00:05:08.182 --> 00:05:11.937
Look at 'em. It's like
they're waiting for a cue.

84
00:05:12.103 --> 00:05:15.931
Now. that's a flash mob.

85
00:05:16.056 --> 00:05:17.943
There.
We lost her.

86
00:05:18.109 --> 00:05:19.027
Can you do anything. Wu?

87
00:05:19.193 --> 00:05:20.336
No. That's it.
The camera's stationary.

88
00:05:20.461 --> 00:05:21.780
She falls out of sight.

89
00:05:21.946 --> 00:05:25.091
That flash mob was our witness pool.

90
00:05:25.216 --> 00:05:26.258
Get this on the news.

91
00:05:26.383 --> 00:05:28.210
Anyone innocent
should come right forward.

92
00:05:28.335 --> 00:05:30.429
I want your full attention on
the streetcar death. all right?

93
00:05:30.554 --> 00:05:32.298
We don't need the city scared
to use public transportation.

94
00:05:32.423 --> 00:05:34.000
Now. Harrison Berman.
the head of the vic's law firm.

95
00:05:34.166 --> 00:05:35.468
he's upset. he's angry.

96
00:05:35.593 --> 00:05:36.711
we're gonna have to deal with this.

97
00:05:36.877 --> 00:05:38.713
You sure this wasn't
a random killing?

98
00:05:38.879 --> 00:05:39.923
It doesn't look like it.

99
00:05:40.214 --> 00:05:43.301
All right. well. anything
you need. you let me know.

100
00:05:44.985 --> 00:05:47.305
Everybody just loved Serena.

101
00:05:47.471 --> 00:05:50.141
You couldn't meet that girl
and not fall for her charms.

102
00:05:50.307 --> 00:05:51.977
Top of her class at law school.

103
00:05:52.143 --> 00:05:53.319
I was a year beneath her.

104
00:05:53.444 --> 00:05:55.480
She kinda took me under her wing.

105
00:05:55.646 --> 00:05:56.639
And was Serena working

106
00:05:56.764 --> 00:05:57.983
on anything that could
have motivated this?

107
00:05:58.149 --> 00:06:00.860
A particular case.
a problematic client. anything?

108
00:06:01.026 --> 00:06:02.812
Not that I remember.

109
00:06:02.937 --> 00:06:04.322
Not everyone likes lawyers.

110
00:06:04.488 --> 00:06:05.781
Well. we'll need to look through

111
00:06:05.906 --> 00:06:07.575
all of Serena's casework
just to be certain.

112
00:06:07.741 --> 00:06:10.972
Sure. Full access.
Whatever you need.

113
00:06:12.313 --> 00:06:14.207
I'll messenger everything over.

114
00:06:14.373 --> 00:06:16.376
Now. what about her personal life?

115
00:06:16.917 --> 00:06:19.261
Boyfriend? Fiance?

116
00:06:19.386 --> 00:06:21.047
I mean. she wasn't
ready to settle down.

117
00:06:21.213 --> 00:06:22.257
She was...

118
00:06:25.015 --> 00:06:28.013
She was really happy
with who she was.

119
00:06:29.882 --> 00:06:30.883
I'm sorry.

120
00:06:34.318 --> 00:06:36.354
You just find
the animal who did this.

121
00:06:36.520 --> 00:06:37.897
We'll do everything we can. sir.

122
00:06:40.574 --> 00:06:41.609
I'm sorry for your loss.

123
00:06:43.110 --> 00:06:45.757
Harper's bee man just buzzed me.

124
00:06:46.947 --> 00:06:48.533
Yeah. I went there.

125
00:06:51.535 --> 00:06:53.212
What makes a guy wanna work every day

126
00:06:53.337 --> 00:06:55.064
in such a dangerous environment?

127
00:06:55.189 --> 00:06:56.682
What. robbery and homicide
too tame for you?

128
00:07:00.294 --> 00:07:01.887
The Queen.

129
00:07:02.012 --> 00:07:03.798
She likes you. Detective.

130
00:07:03.964 --> 00:07:06.341
Don't be fooled.

131
00:07:06.466 --> 00:07:07.969
She's fiercely protective
of her hive.

132
00:07:08.135 --> 00:07:11.147
It's unusual that she should
show herself like this.

133
00:07:11.272 --> 00:07:12.581
So. Mr. Spinella...

134
00:07:12.706 --> 00:07:14.400
Professor.

135
00:07:14.525 --> 00:07:16.035
Professor Spinella.

136
00:07:16.160 --> 00:07:17.520
Were you able to analyze the apitoxin

137
00:07:17.645 --> 00:07:18.480
that our coroner sent over?

138
00:07:18.646 --> 00:07:21.316
Indeed I did. Detective.

139
00:07:21.482 --> 00:07:23.276
And?

140
00:07:23.442 --> 00:07:25.612
Well. it's not synthetic.

141
00:07:25.778 --> 00:07:27.396
You mean someone harvested

142
00:07:27.521 --> 00:07:29.657
50 milligrams of apitoxin
from actual bees?

143
00:07:29.823 --> 00:07:31.076
Apparently so.

144
00:07:31.242 --> 00:07:33.078
You see. natural apitoxin
carries geographical traits.

145
00:07:33.244 --> 00:07:35.413
Signatures.

146
00:07:35.579 --> 00:07:37.582
By analysis of the chemical
ratios of the venom.

147
00:07:37.748 --> 00:07:40.126
one can determine
the geo-regional origins.

148
00:07:40.292 --> 00:07:41.844
So where did the apitoxin

149
00:07:41.969 --> 00:07:43.463
that killed
Serena Dunbrook come from?

150
00:07:43.629 --> 00:07:46.508
Well. I'd definitely
categorize it as. uh. exotic.

151
00:07:46.674 --> 00:07:51.520
Which would normally mean
China. Africa. France...

152
00:07:51.645 --> 00:07:55.224
However. your apitoxin shows
levels of phospholipase too.

153
00:07:55.349 --> 00:07:56.267
that I've never seen before.

154
00:07:56.433 --> 00:08:00.605
This apitoxin has no known origin.

155
00:08:00.771 --> 00:08:04.083
Uh. excuse me.

156
00:08:04.208 --> 00:08:05.235
Unknown origin?

157
00:08:05.401 --> 00:08:06.752
What is this. some Sci-Fi crap?

158
00:08:06.877 --> 00:08:08.363
That stuff couldn't
just come out of nowhere.

159
00:08:08.529 --> 00:08:09.614
What. do you think
he's hiding something?

160
00:08:09.780 --> 00:08:10.698
Detectives.

161
00:08:10.864 --> 00:08:14.452
In case I'm on that list of yours.

162
00:08:14.618 --> 00:08:17.463
harvesting apitoxin
in that amount would require

163
00:08:17.588 --> 00:08:18.964
much more sophisticated equipment

164
00:08:19.089 --> 00:08:20.458
than I have at my disposal.

165
00:08:20.624 --> 00:08:22.168
Besides. I was at the Howard Johnson

166
00:08:22.334 --> 00:08:23.619
in Eugene last night

167
00:08:23.744 --> 00:08:26.840
for this year's Oregon
beekeeper's con.

168
00:08:27.006 --> 00:08:29.968
Pretty crowded convention?

169
00:08:30.134 --> 00:08:32.995
Well. there's 12 of us. actually.

170
00:08:33.120 --> 00:08:34.305
Anything else I can help you with?

171
00:08:34.471 --> 00:08:36.474
No. Professor.
We'll be in touch.

172
00:08:40.327 --> 00:08:41.896
A streetcar full of dancers.

173
00:08:42.062 --> 00:08:43.815
and 12 bee geeks in a motel room?

174
00:08:43.981 --> 00:08:46.441
Your suspect pool's
getting bigger. huh?

175
00:08:46.566 --> 00:08:48.194
T.V. coverage paid off.

176
00:08:48.360 --> 00:08:50.713
Say hi to your flash mob.

177
00:08:50.838 --> 00:08:52.298
'Scuse me.

178
00:08:52.423 --> 00:08:54.116
22 so far.

179
00:08:54.241 --> 00:08:56.135
By the way. the Captain's been taking

180
00:08:56.260 --> 00:08:57.653
a keen interest in this one.

181
00:08:57.778 --> 00:08:59.247
He's even asking me what's going on.

182
00:08:59.413 --> 00:09:01.724
Listen. then do us a favor.

183
00:09:01.849 --> 00:09:03.460
While we talk to the village people.

184
00:09:03.626 --> 00:09:05.003
can you check out the alibi

185
00:09:05.169 --> 00:09:06.546
of Professor Spinella last night?

186
00:09:06.712 --> 00:09:09.841
Some convention
at the Ho-Jo's in Eugene.

187
00:09:10.007 --> 00:09:11.885
And get us the name of every
beekeeper who was there.

188
00:09:13.079 --> 00:09:14.554
No problem.

189
00:09:15.932 --> 00:09:17.806
Have fun with your interrogations.

190
00:09:17.931 --> 00:09:18.932
We will.

191
00:09:20.434 --> 00:09:22.244
- I didn't know anyone...
- On that streetcar.

192
00:09:22.369 --> 00:09:24.079
- Every one of 'em was
- a stranger.

193
00:09:24.355 --> 00:09:25.023
Then why were you there?

194
00:09:25.189 --> 00:09:26.315
I got the invite.

195
00:09:26.440 --> 00:09:28.350
- Totally random...
- Tweet. telling me a...

196
00:09:28.475 --> 00:09:30.252
- Time and a...
- Place. and what to do.

197
00:09:30.377 --> 00:09:31.696
- Get on at...
- Yamhill...

198
00:09:31.862 --> 00:09:34.823
And dance the Y.M.C.A.

199
00:09:34.948 --> 00:09:36.117
We've been told.

200
00:09:36.283 --> 00:09:39.595
- Yeah. And then. immediately...
- Get off at alder.

201
00:09:39.720 --> 00:09:41.096
I didn't see that girl.

202
00:09:41.221 --> 00:09:42.331
There were a lot of us on there.

203
00:09:42.456 --> 00:09:43.917
We were just dancing. having fun.

204
00:09:44.083 --> 00:09:45.434
- How was I supposed...
- To know someone...

205
00:09:45.559 --> 00:09:48.963
Was getting killed?

206
00:09:49.129 --> 00:09:50.757
Can I go now?

207
00:09:50.923 --> 00:09:52.241
Actually. no. Doug.

208
00:09:52.366 --> 00:09:53.968
I'd like to go over it again.
if you don't mind.

209
00:09:54.134 --> 00:09:55.261
From the beginning?

210
00:09:55.427 --> 00:09:58.223
Well. yeah. unless you know
what happens in the end.

211
00:10:01.308 --> 00:10:03.228
Well. like I said...

212
00:10:03.394 --> 00:10:06.147
I got the same invitation
as everybody else did.

213
00:10:06.313 --> 00:10:08.650
I figured I'd go have
some fun with some strangers.

214
00:10:08.816 --> 00:10:10.125
It just sounds
like there's an echo in here.

215
00:10:10.250 --> 00:10:11.110
'cause I keep hearing

216
00:10:11.276 --> 00:10:13.238
the same thing. over and over again.

217
00:10:13.404 --> 00:10:15.448
Okay. can I see the tweet?

218
00:10:15.614 --> 00:10:17.075
A tech-savvy guy like yourself.

219
00:10:17.241 --> 00:10:20.419
I'm sure you still have it
on your phone. right?

220
00:10:20.544 --> 00:10:22.504
Um...

221
00:10:22.629 --> 00:10:26.960
I got some personal stuff on there.

222
00:10:27.126 --> 00:10:29.812
All right.

223
00:10:29.937 --> 00:10:31.631
Well. let's talk about the victim.

224
00:10:31.797 --> 00:10:33.849
So Serena Dunbrook
got on the streetcar

225
00:10:33.974 --> 00:10:35.084
around the same time as you. right?

226
00:10:35.209 --> 00:10:36.094
She's a pretty girl.

227
00:10:36.260 --> 00:10:38.821
She stood right behind you.

228
00:10:38.946 --> 00:10:41.808
You know. did you smell her perfume?

229
00:10:41.974 --> 00:10:43.459
Did it turn you on
to be rubbed up against her?

230
00:10:43.584 --> 00:10:44.769
No.

231
00:10:44.935 --> 00:10:47.272
Hey. come on. Doug.
We have you on the videotape.

232
00:10:47.438 --> 00:10:48.564
I was on the other side.

233
00:10:48.689 --> 00:10:49.607
Really?

234
00:10:49.773 --> 00:10:51.600
Because in your previous statement.

235
00:10:51.725 --> 00:10:55.655
you said you didn't see her
at all. so which one is it?

236
00:10:55.821 --> 00:10:58.340
Come on.
Let me see the phone. Doug.

237
00:10:58.465 --> 00:11:01.786
Unless you're hiding something.

238
00:11:21.054 --> 00:11:22.931
Ag waiver turned up a dummy account

239
00:11:23.056 --> 00:11:24.817
opened with a spam e-mail.

240
00:11:24.942 --> 00:11:26.728
All it takes is half a brain
and a laptop

241
00:11:26.894 --> 00:11:28.521
to manipulate an IP address.

242
00:11:28.687 --> 00:11:30.857
Benefit of social media...

243
00:11:31.023 --> 00:11:35.153
Anyone can arrange cover
for a murder.

244
00:11:35.319 --> 00:11:39.657
You get something
off this Doug shellow guy?

245
00:11:42.785 --> 00:11:44.586
Yeah.

246
00:11:44.711 --> 00:11:47.046
I think I just did.

247
00:11:57.090 --> 00:12:01.471
Abandoned paper mill?
This doesn't look like home.

248
00:12:10.729 --> 00:12:12.731
You know anything
about primrose paper?

249
00:12:12.856 --> 00:12:14.299
I've heard of it.
That's all.

250
00:12:14.424 --> 00:12:16.434
Old family business.
been here forever.

251
00:12:16.559 --> 00:12:17.602
Do you really think

252
00:12:17.727 --> 00:12:18.970
Doug shellow and John Coleman
know each other?

253
00:12:19.095 --> 00:12:22.241
Let's hope letting them go pays off.

254
00:12:41.510 --> 00:12:45.163
Hello. conspiracy.

255
00:12:45.288 --> 00:12:48.726
So much for everybody
claiming to be strangers.

256
00:12:52.595 --> 00:12:54.806
Who is that?

257
00:12:54.931 --> 00:12:58.827
I can't get a good look at her.

258
00:13:09.212 --> 00:13:11.947
Oh. run!

259
00:13:15.218 --> 00:13:18.453
Aah!

260
00:13:21.891 --> 00:13:24.971
Get in this office!

261
00:13:32.986 --> 00:13:35.146
What the hell's going on?
Where'd those bees come from?

262
00:13:35.271 --> 00:13:36.281
I don't know.

263
00:13:36.406 --> 00:13:38.901
Here. use some of these.
Here.

264
00:13:45.582 --> 00:13:49.818
Oh! I've never seen
so many damn bees in my life!

265
00:13:56.659 --> 00:14:00.923
Wait. Where'd they go?

266
00:14:01.089 --> 00:14:03.007
Maybe they're hiding. waiting for us.

267
00:14:03.132 --> 00:14:07.436
Yeah. I don't think bees hide.

268
00:14:13.185 --> 00:14:18.107
Oh. man. I got at least
a couple dozen bee stings.

269
00:14:18.273 --> 00:14:20.024
This is crazy.

270
00:14:20.149 --> 00:14:21.443
Someone gets killed with bee venom.

271
00:14:21.568 --> 00:14:22.894
and we get attacked by a swarm?

272
00:14:23.019 --> 00:14:24.447
Yeah. I don't think
it's a coincidence.

273
00:14:24.613 --> 00:14:29.660
Yeah. maybe Wu was right
about a giant killer bee.

274
00:14:34.873 --> 00:14:35.790
Come on.
Let's get- ow! Some help.

275
00:14:35.915 --> 00:14:37.794
You're a bigger baby than he is.

276
00:14:37.960 --> 00:14:39.504
Two beers. one water.

277
00:14:39.670 --> 00:14:41.964
Bees usually sting
when threatened or provoked.

278
00:14:42.130 --> 00:14:43.216
You kick a hive or something?

279
00:14:43.382 --> 00:14:44.649
No. they just came out of nowhere

280
00:14:44.774 --> 00:14:46.135
and headed straight for yours truly.

281
00:14:46.301 --> 00:14:48.221
Aw. maybe you're their flower.

282
00:14:48.387 --> 00:14:49.472
Excuse me?

283
00:14:49.638 --> 00:14:51.182
Bees are highly
effective communicators.

284
00:14:51.348 --> 00:14:53.809
A scout will fly around till
they find the perfect flower.

285
00:14:53.975 --> 00:14:54.852
then it goes back to the hive

286
00:14:55.018 --> 00:14:56.854
and signals the others to follow.

287
00:14:57.020 --> 00:14:58.606
You learned all that in vet school?

288
00:14:58.772 --> 00:15:00.316
Nope. Animal planet.

289
00:15:00.482 --> 00:15:03.027
Well. they say anything about
training bees to attack people?

290
00:15:03.193 --> 00:15:04.035
That sounds more like a bad movie.

291
00:15:04.160 --> 00:15:05.403
Ew...

292
00:15:05.528 --> 00:15:07.406
Well. shellow and Coleman
are still our best leads.

293
00:15:07.572 --> 00:15:08.740
I just put out an APB.

294
00:15:08.865 --> 00:15:10.117
What about our mystery woman?

295
00:15:10.283 --> 00:15:12.794
Well. two guys were reporting to her.

296
00:15:12.919 --> 00:15:14.879
So there's gotta be a connection
between the three of them.

297
00:15:15.004 --> 00:15:17.549
the mill. and Serena Dunbrook.

298
00:15:17.674 --> 00:15:21.504
Let's take a look at
the case files burman sent us.

299
00:15:21.670 --> 00:15:23.756
Uh-uh. my patient is not
doing anything but resting

300
00:15:24.047 --> 00:15:27.141
and not scratching
for the next eight hours.

301
00:15:27.266 --> 00:15:28.309
Dude. if you were a dog.

302
00:15:28.434 --> 00:15:29.627
I would've already tranquilized you.

303
00:15:29.752 --> 00:15:30.638
She's right.

304
00:15:30.804 --> 00:15:32.473
I got this.
You go to sleep.

305
00:15:32.639 --> 00:15:36.811
- Thanks. doc.
- Bye.

306
00:15:37.978 --> 00:15:42.807
I know. You're sorry.
but you have to work.

307
00:15:42.932 --> 00:15:47.238
I just thought I'd let you know
what you'll be missing.

308
00:15:53.275 --> 00:15:55.119
Look. I just have to
do some research.

309
00:15:55.244 --> 00:15:56.431
I won't be long.

310
00:15:56.556 --> 00:15:58.765
Yeah. well. you've been
turning this no-sleep thing

311
00:15:58.890 --> 00:16:00.209
into an art form lately.

312
00:16:01.250 --> 00:16:02.251
Night.

313
00:17:06.566 --> 00:17:09.694
A Hexenbiest mark
can be found under the tongue

314
00:17:09.819 --> 00:17:12.740
in both human form and morphed form.

315
00:17:29.505 --> 00:17:31.467
Hey. It's me.

316
00:17:31.633 --> 00:17:34.470
Did you hear about that girl
who was murdered on the tram?

317
00:17:42.394 --> 00:17:44.529
Whoa! Easy. there. five-o.

318
00:17:44.654 --> 00:17:46.691
You called me. remember?

319
00:17:46.857 --> 00:17:49.500
Man.

320
00:17:49.625 --> 00:17:51.821
Don't you have a partner
for this stuff?

321
00:17:51.987 --> 00:17:53.004
Yeah. sure. because if I told him

322
00:17:53.129 --> 00:17:54.323
my two main suspects
turned into bees.

323
00:17:54.489 --> 00:17:55.606
he'd completely understand.

324
00:17:55.731 --> 00:17:58.409
Lucky me.

325
00:17:58.534 --> 00:17:59.877
So mellifers. huh?

326
00:18:00.002 --> 00:18:00.912
Yeah. they had something to do

327
00:18:01.037 --> 00:18:01.913
with a murder
on a Portland streetcar.

328
00:18:02.038 --> 00:18:02.957
Murder?

329
00:18:03.123 --> 00:18:04.449
Not really their shtick.

330
00:18:04.574 --> 00:18:05.883
Well. bees bite. don't they?

331
00:18:06.008 --> 00:18:07.885
- Yeah. but only when...
- Threatened. I know.

332
00:18:08.010 --> 00:18:09.587
But I read in the book
that they also have

333
00:18:09.712 --> 00:18:11.589
something to do
with balancing the ecotone.

334
00:18:11.714 --> 00:18:13.057
- Huh.
- What does that mean?

335
00:18:13.182 --> 00:18:14.959
That's just
some fancy-pants mumbo jumbo

336
00:18:15.084 --> 00:18:16.637
for saying they're
like gossips. you know?

337
00:18:16.803 --> 00:18:18.563
A creature community switchboard.

338
00:18:18.688 --> 00:18:20.850
Or a social media.

339
00:18:21.016 --> 00:18:22.667
Huh.

340
00:18:22.792 --> 00:18:24.502
And if a mellifer
sends out a message.

341
00:18:24.627 --> 00:18:27.064
it definitely means something
sketchy's going on somewhere.

342
00:18:27.480 --> 00:18:30.074
Well. Hank and I were attacked
by a swarm of bees earlier.

343
00:18:30.199 --> 00:18:32.778
if that's sketchy enough for you.

344
00:18:35.322 --> 00:18:39.076
We were following two guys
who turned out to be mellifers.

345
00:18:39.242 --> 00:18:43.087
And they met a woman.

346
00:18:43.212 --> 00:18:45.790
Yeah? And?

347
00:18:45.915 --> 00:18:46.891
What. you think I know everything

348
00:18:47.016 --> 00:18:48.461
about every creature out there?

349
00:18:48.627 --> 00:18:51.005
No. I don't need you for what
you know. I need your nose.

350
00:18:51.454 --> 00:18:53.064
Oh. I get it.

351
00:18:53.189 --> 00:18:54.599
So little Timmy's stuck in a well.

352
00:18:54.724 --> 00:18:56.167
you need Lassie to come find him?

353
00:18:56.292 --> 00:18:58.502
Boy. you really know how to
butter a guy up for a favor.

354
00:18:58.627 --> 00:19:00.264
I got a bottle
of '78 Bordeaux in my trunk.

355
00:19:00.430 --> 00:19:02.183
I can maybe catch a scent.

356
00:19:02.349 --> 00:19:04.208
Okay.

357
00:19:04.333 --> 00:19:06.310
Now. you said mellifers
deliver messages.

358
00:19:07.436 --> 00:19:08.346
What kind of message is it

359
00:19:08.471 --> 00:19:09.690
when they murder an innocent woman?

360
00:19:09.856 --> 00:19:14.028
Maybe she wasn't so innocent.

361
00:19:21.984 --> 00:19:24.245
Mellifers only have
one natural enemy.

362
00:19:24.370 --> 00:19:25.414
Hexenbiests.

363
00:19:25.580 --> 00:19:27.249
Look at you. hitting the books.

364
00:19:32.212 --> 00:19:34.038
Oh. yeah.

365
00:19:34.163 --> 00:19:37.542
I'm definitely getting
a female scent here.

366
00:19:37.667 --> 00:19:39.376
Undeniable.

367
00:19:39.501 --> 00:19:41.746
You're that sure?

368
00:19:41.871 --> 00:19:46.268
No. her perfume.
It's called "undeniable."

369
00:19:46.434 --> 00:19:47.686
Hey. wait up.

370
00:19:47.852 --> 00:19:51.606
Don't you dare say. "heel."

371
00:19:51.731 --> 00:19:52.824
Well. they didn't come in here.

372
00:19:52.949 --> 00:19:53.891
We saw them leave the mill.

373
00:19:54.016 --> 00:19:58.946
Hey. The nose knows.

374
00:19:59.071 --> 00:20:02.076
I am getting a big-time
whiff of her in here.

375
00:20:06.045 --> 00:20:08.040
Maybe she left something behind.

376
00:20:10.458 --> 00:20:12.294
Oh. yeah.

377
00:20:12.460 --> 00:20:15.847
Scent's real strong.

378
00:20:19.642 --> 00:20:23.638
She could come back at some point.

379
00:20:23.805 --> 00:20:27.258
Maybe we could crack
that Bordeaux while we wait.

380
00:20:27.383 --> 00:20:28.477
Her name's Melissa Wincroft.

381
00:20:28.643 --> 00:20:31.662
Whoa.

382
00:20:31.787 --> 00:20:34.649
Did you just. like. Grimm that
in some kind of telepathic way?

383
00:20:34.816 --> 00:20:37.444
No. I read it off an envelope.

384
00:20:37.610 --> 00:20:40.471
Melissa Wincroft. owner and CEO.

385
00:20:40.596 --> 00:20:41.472
This must've been her office.

386
00:20:41.597 --> 00:20:44.625
That's cheating.

387
00:20:44.750 --> 00:20:46.829
Well. I sniffed her out.

388
00:20:46.995 --> 00:20:49.665
Good boy.

389
00:20:56.004 --> 00:20:59.258
Yeah. this is definitely her place.

390
00:21:29.412 --> 00:21:31.122
This is so the part
of the horror movie

391
00:21:31.247 --> 00:21:32.990
where the sidekick gets it.

392
00:21:33.115 --> 00:21:34.335
Just stay close.

393
00:21:55.705 --> 00:21:56.781
What is it?

394
00:21:56.906 --> 00:21:57.733
Shh.

395
00:22:13.723 --> 00:22:17.625
Tell me we are not going upstairs.

396
00:22:17.750 --> 00:22:20.464
We're going upstairs.

397
00:23:09.220 --> 00:23:11.514
Damn.

398
00:23:11.639 --> 00:23:13.299
I know. right?

399
00:23:13.424 --> 00:23:15.301
Forensics says this stuff
is a preliminary match

400
00:23:15.426 --> 00:23:17.303
to the apitoxin in Serena's system.

401
00:23:17.428 --> 00:23:18.639
That clears our beekeepers.

402
00:23:18.764 --> 00:23:20.389
Which makes
Melissa Wincroft our primary.

403
00:23:20.514 --> 00:23:22.275
that clears if we could find her.

404
00:23:22.400 --> 00:23:24.393
She didn't sell this place
or buy a new one.

405
00:23:24.518 --> 00:23:27.647
It's like she just picked up
and disappeared.

406
00:23:27.772 --> 00:23:29.315
Now. can you tell me how in the hell

407
00:23:29.440 --> 00:23:31.035
you found this woman and her hive?

408
00:23:31.201 --> 00:23:33.569
Well. it's all in the legal files.

409
00:23:33.694 --> 00:23:35.071
Read 'em last night.

410
00:23:35.196 --> 00:23:36.206
Everything's connected...

411
00:23:36.372 --> 00:23:39.408
Shellow. Coleman. the mill.
even Serena.

412
00:23:39.533 --> 00:23:40.586
Well. you could've called me.

413
00:23:40.752 --> 00:23:43.129
Hey. doctor told you to rest.

414
00:23:43.254 --> 00:23:45.674
Yeah. fine.

415
00:23:45.840 --> 00:23:46.883
All right.

416
00:23:47.008 --> 00:23:48.427
So. connect the dots.

417
00:23:48.593 --> 00:23:51.387
Well. messy class-action
lawsuit about a year ago.

418
00:23:51.512 --> 00:23:52.972
Serena represented ameri-mill

419
00:23:53.097 --> 00:23:54.475
in a hostile takeover
of primrose paper.

420
00:23:54.641 --> 00:23:57.343
Uh. the employees tried
to fight it... they lost.

421
00:23:57.468 --> 00:23:58.761
Let me guess. two of those employees

422
00:23:58.886 --> 00:24:00.230
were Doug shellow and John Coleman.

423
00:24:00.396 --> 00:24:02.882
Exactly.
Melissa Wincroft was their boss.

424
00:24:03.007 --> 00:24:05.017
Her family owned and operated
the mill for over a century.

425
00:24:05.142 --> 00:24:06.195
She had the most to lose.

426
00:24:06.361 --> 00:24:07.737
So she's taking revenge on Serena

427
00:24:07.862 --> 00:24:08.989
for getting her company shut down.

428
00:24:09.155 --> 00:24:10.824
- Mm-hmm.
- Detectives.

429
00:24:10.990 --> 00:24:12.625
Sergeant Wu just called
from Chapman square.

430
00:24:12.750 --> 00:24:15.579
There's been another
flash mob murder.

431
00:24:23.828 --> 00:24:25.964
Another tweet. another flash mob.

432
00:24:26.130 --> 00:24:28.174
This time. death by <i>hokey pokey.</i>

433
00:24:28.299 --> 00:24:29.759
Witnesses say the victim was doing

434
00:24:29.884 --> 00:24:31.377
her morning yoga routine
when it started.

435
00:24:31.502 --> 00:24:32.878
Eye in the sky caught it all.

436
00:24:33.003 --> 00:24:34.180
Shellow or Coleman in the group?

437
00:24:34.305 --> 00:24:36.350
Nope. Whole new set
of flash mobbers this time.

438
00:24:36.640 --> 00:24:38.050
But unis grabbed shellow
and Coleman about an hour ago.

439
00:24:38.175 --> 00:24:39.186
They're at the precinct.

440
00:24:39.352 --> 00:24:43.065
Both are staying silent
until they lawyer up.

441
00:24:44.899 --> 00:24:47.319
Tell me you got a solid lead on this.

442
00:24:47.485 --> 00:24:50.446
We're zeroing in
on a suspect... Melissa Wincroft.

443
00:24:50.571 --> 00:24:51.781
That's Camilla Gotleib.

444
00:24:51.948 --> 00:24:54.660
She was on the primrose paper
case with Serena.

445
00:24:54.826 --> 00:24:56.736
Two dead lawyers from the same firm?

446
00:24:56.861 --> 00:24:58.247
I'd say we got ourselves a pattern.

447
00:24:58.413 --> 00:24:59.748
There was a third lawyer on the case.

448
00:24:59.914 --> 00:25:02.041
I read it in the files.

449
00:25:02.166 --> 00:25:03.326
This is Detective Burkhardt.

450
00:25:03.451 --> 00:25:05.077
Send a unit to
Berman. Rautbort and associates

451
00:25:05.202 --> 00:25:07.413
and take an attorney
into protective custody.

452
00:25:07.538 --> 00:25:08.882
Her name's adalind schade.

453
00:25:12.877 --> 00:25:14.430
Miss schade.

454
00:25:18.641 --> 00:25:20.519
You.

455
00:25:22.895 --> 00:25:23.939
I'm Captain Renard.

456
00:25:24.105 --> 00:25:26.682
These are Detectives
Griffin and Burkhardt.

457
00:25:26.807 --> 00:25:28.986
Detectives.
Thank you.

458
00:25:29.152 --> 00:25:30.703
You can thank Detective Burkhardt.

459
00:25:30.828 --> 00:25:32.355
He's the one who figured it all out.

460
00:25:32.480 --> 00:25:34.616
Actually. I'm still trying
to piece it all together.

461
00:25:34.782 --> 00:25:38.344
We need to ask you a few
questions. if you're up for it.

462
00:25:38.469 --> 00:25:40.379
Can I offer you a cup of coffee?

463
00:25:40.504 --> 00:25:42.989
Thanks.

464
00:25:48.345 --> 00:25:50.256
Hey. Nick.

465
00:25:50.381 --> 00:25:51.216
Nick.

466
00:25:54.135 --> 00:25:55.127
You all right?

467
00:25:55.252 --> 00:25:59.098
You look like you've seen a ghost.

468
00:25:59.223 --> 00:26:00.559
You know this woman?

469
00:26:00.725 --> 00:26:04.897
For a second. I thought
I'd seen her somewhere before.

470
00:26:05.063 --> 00:26:06.231
But you're not sure.

471
00:26:11.068 --> 00:26:12.178
There's a killer out there

472
00:26:12.303 --> 00:26:14.281
that's already hit
two of her coworkers.

473
00:26:14.505 --> 00:26:17.117
So. if you know something
about adalind schade.

474
00:26:17.283 --> 00:26:19.578
now's the time to share it.

475
00:26:19.744 --> 00:26:22.748
I don't know anything more
about her than you do.

476
00:26:29.486 --> 00:26:32.925
Well. then just. um. stay
on your game and keep her safe.

477
00:26:35.093 --> 00:26:36.762
Don't want her to be number three.

478
00:26:41.974 --> 00:26:43.685
I need to see their tongues.

479
00:26:43.851 --> 00:26:45.312
Whatever floats your boat.

480
00:26:45.478 --> 00:26:48.315
The bodies were so swollen.

481
00:26:48.481 --> 00:26:50.983
I had to cut 'em out
just to get a look inside.

482
00:26:51.108 --> 00:26:54.904
Here they are.

483
00:27:01.577 --> 00:27:05.874
Is there anything strange
on either of them?

484
00:27:06.040 --> 00:27:08.502
What made that mark?

485
00:27:08.751 --> 00:27:10.669
I thought that was weird too.

486
00:27:10.794 --> 00:27:13.173
Here.

487
00:27:15.198 --> 00:27:16.093
See?

488
00:27:16.259 --> 00:27:18.677
But they're not tattoos.

489
00:27:18.802 --> 00:27:22.057
These marks have nothing
to do with their deaths.

490
00:27:22.273 --> 00:27:25.185
Who would do this hideous thing
to these girls?

491
00:27:27.478 --> 00:27:29.355
Ms. Wincroft.
please answer the question

492
00:27:29.480 --> 00:27:31.457
regarding the quarterly earnings.

493
00:27:31.582 --> 00:27:34.560
This is not about the money.

494
00:27:34.685 --> 00:27:36.697
They are trying to get rid of us.

495
00:27:36.863 --> 00:27:39.992
These workers...
Everyone. we are a family.

496
00:27:40.158 --> 00:27:42.703
And they're trying to shut us
down to get us out of the way.

497
00:27:42.869 --> 00:27:46.872
Your quarterly earnings.
Ms. Wincroft.

498
00:27:46.997 --> 00:27:51.377
I know who's behind this.

499
00:27:51.502 --> 00:27:56.048
And they're not gonna
get away with it.

500
00:27:56.173 --> 00:27:58.317
That sounds like a threat to me.

501
00:27:58.442 --> 00:28:01.513
I can't believe she could've
done this to Serena and Camilla.

502
00:28:01.679 --> 00:28:03.973
We just don't want you to be next.

503
00:28:04.098 --> 00:28:05.642
Now. miss schade...

504
00:28:05.808 --> 00:28:08.227
Please. call me adalind.
All my friends do.

505
00:28:08.394 --> 00:28:11.063
All your friends are dead.

506
00:28:11.230 --> 00:28:13.399
I mean. it just seems more personal

507
00:28:13.524 --> 00:28:15.167
than a business transaction to me...

508
00:28:15.292 --> 00:28:16.528
Eye for an eye sort of thing...

509
00:28:16.694 --> 00:28:20.406
Like you hurt someone
close to her or something.

510
00:28:20.531 --> 00:28:23.201
Some people don't get
the big picture.

511
00:28:23.367 --> 00:28:24.326
I was just doing my job.

512
00:28:24.451 --> 00:28:25.871
Hey. so am I.

513
00:28:26.037 --> 00:28:27.414
Just trying to get
to the truth. here.

514
00:28:27.580 --> 00:28:29.750
Unless miss schade
has something to hide.

515
00:28:29.916 --> 00:28:34.880
No more than you do. Detective.

516
00:28:35.046 --> 00:28:36.715
Look. I wish I could tell you

517
00:28:36.881 --> 00:28:40.052
something more
about Melissa Wincroft.

518
00:28:40.218 --> 00:28:41.553
but I really didn't know her.

519
00:28:41.719 --> 00:28:44.797
I told you. it wasn't personal.

520
00:28:44.922 --> 00:28:46.016
Yeah. well. maybe not for you.

521
00:28:46.182 --> 00:28:47.684
But if someone tried to take

522
00:28:47.850 --> 00:28:49.561
something important away from me.

523
00:28:49.727 --> 00:28:51.855
I'd take it very personally.

524
00:28:52.021 --> 00:28:53.357
You know. let's take a break.

525
00:28:53.523 --> 00:28:55.233
Excuse us. adalind.

526
00:28:58.528 --> 00:29:00.238
You coming?

527
00:29:05.576 --> 00:29:06.685
What's up with you?

528
00:29:06.810 --> 00:29:08.220
You're treating her
like she's the perp.

529
00:29:08.345 --> 00:29:09.572
I don't trust her.

530
00:29:09.697 --> 00:29:11.540
You don't have to.
You just have to protect her.

531
00:29:11.665 --> 00:29:14.017
Come on. we gotta track down
Melissa Wincroft.

532
00:29:17.880 --> 00:29:19.465
Burkhardt remembers me.

533
00:29:19.632 --> 00:29:21.718
I pushed him.
but he's keeping it to himself.

534
00:29:21.884 --> 00:29:24.388
Maybe he's just waiting
to get me alone.

535
00:29:24.554 --> 00:29:27.891
I told you. I won't let
anything happen to you.

536
00:29:28.057 --> 00:29:32.077
Is that what you told
Serena and Camilla?

537
00:29:32.202 --> 00:29:34.813
Serena and Camilla are not you.

538
00:29:34.938 --> 00:29:37.692
I can take care of myself.

539
00:29:37.858 --> 00:29:39.569
Just find this queen.

540
00:29:39.735 --> 00:29:42.239
Or I'm not the only one
who's gonna get stung.

541
00:29:47.319 --> 00:29:48.618
Got it. thanks.

542
00:29:49.119 --> 00:29:51.163
No credit card activity. no travel.

543
00:29:51.288 --> 00:29:52.998
no sign of Melissa Wincroft
in the system.

544
00:29:53.123 --> 00:29:54.499
She's got no known family.

545
00:29:54.624 --> 00:29:55.834
Friends?

546
00:29:55.959 --> 00:29:57.753
Well. we know about
John Coleman and Doug shellow.

547
00:29:57.878 --> 00:30:01.174
but I doubt she's
gonna be calling them.

548
00:30:01.757 --> 00:30:04.094
That look usually gets us in trouble.

549
00:30:04.260 --> 00:30:06.695
Well. she might not be
getting in touch with them.

550
00:30:06.820 --> 00:30:08.265
What if they got in touch with her?

551
00:30:08.431 --> 00:30:10.165
Wu said Shellow's not cooperating

552
00:30:10.290 --> 00:30:11.466
until he sees a lawyer.

553
00:30:11.591 --> 00:30:12.684
We don't need him to cooperate.

554
00:30:12.809 --> 00:30:14.670
We just need him to do
what he does best...

555
00:30:14.795 --> 00:30:16.171
Send a message.

556
00:30:16.296 --> 00:30:18.483
And he doesn't know
we're protecting adalind schade.

557
00:30:18.649 --> 00:30:21.278
And neither does Melissa Wincroft.

558
00:30:21.444 --> 00:30:23.812
Hey. Doug.

559
00:30:23.937 --> 00:30:26.867
How you doing?
You hungry?

560
00:30:27.033 --> 00:30:29.411
You and I have
some unfinished business.

561
00:30:29.577 --> 00:30:33.582
So why don't we pick up
where we left off?

562
00:30:37.417 --> 00:30:39.867
You were about
to show me some tweets.

563
00:30:41.254 --> 00:30:42.591
Tweet this.

564
00:30:42.757 --> 00:30:45.200
I don't have to do anything
until my lawyer gets here.

565
00:30:45.325 --> 00:30:47.035
Oh. Doug.

566
00:30:47.160 --> 00:30:48.722
We have you
at the scene of the crime.

567
00:30:48.888 --> 00:30:51.308
We tailed you to a meeting
with our prime suspect.

568
00:30:51.474 --> 00:30:53.560
You will do seven to ten
on conspiracy alone.

569
00:30:53.726 --> 00:30:55.103
no matter how good your lawyer is.

570
00:30:55.269 --> 00:31:00.484
So why do you wanna keep
protecting Melissa Wincroft?

571
00:31:02.008 --> 00:31:05.822
There's gonna be
another victim. isn't there?

572
00:31:05.988 --> 00:31:07.741
Tell me...

573
00:31:07.907 --> 00:31:10.202
Who is it?

574
00:31:10.368 --> 00:31:13.195
Doug. come on. do yourself a favor.

575
00:31:13.320 --> 00:31:15.624
Who is Melissa Wincroft's
next target?

576
00:31:15.790 --> 00:31:17.125
Nick. Captain needs to see you. now.

577
00:31:17.291 --> 00:31:20.936
Hank. I'm in the middle of something.

578
00:31:21.061 --> 00:31:23.131
This isn't over.

579
00:31:36.644 --> 00:31:38.553
Oscar-worthy performance. de niro.

580
00:31:38.678 --> 00:31:40.690
- Middle-school drama club.
- This better work.

581
00:31:40.856 --> 00:31:43.443
It will.
It's in his nature.

582
00:31:47.488 --> 00:31:48.730
Come on. Doug.

583
00:31:48.855 --> 00:31:50.825
Phone's right there. buddy.
Take the bait.

584
00:32:02.285 --> 00:32:04.346
There it is. Wu.

585
00:32:04.471 --> 00:32:05.380
On it.

586
00:32:05.505 --> 00:32:06.681
How quick does this stuff work?

587
00:32:06.806 --> 00:32:07.949
There.

588
00:32:08.074 --> 00:32:09.636
He just sent a direct message
to a blocked user.

589
00:32:09.802 --> 00:32:10.971
Well. can you...

590
00:32:11.137 --> 00:32:12.854
Of course I can. I'm Asian.

591
00:32:12.979 --> 00:32:13.890
Okay.

592
00:32:14.056 --> 00:32:15.057
Here's the message.

593
00:32:15.182 --> 00:32:19.127
"They don't know. As open."

594
00:32:19.252 --> 00:32:20.855
"As open."

595
00:32:21.021 --> 00:32:24.099
"As."

596
00:32:24.224 --> 00:32:27.654
A.S.--Adalind schade.

597
00:32:27.820 --> 00:32:30.365
He just told Melissa Wincroft
to make the move.

598
00:32:51.302 --> 00:32:55.230
You're home early. miss schade.

599
00:32:55.355 --> 00:32:57.142
She's headed your way.

600
00:33:08.702 --> 00:33:10.905
Which floor. miss schade?

601
00:33:15.201 --> 00:33:16.453
Bird's in the nest.

602
00:33:16.619 --> 00:33:17.652
Nice work.

603
00:33:17.777 --> 00:33:21.490
Now. let's hope Melissa Wincroft
takes the bait.

604
00:33:21.615 --> 00:33:23.291
Do you really think this'll work?

605
00:33:23.416 --> 00:33:25.378
Well. we've gotta smoke her
out of her hiding place somehow.

606
00:33:25.544 --> 00:33:27.881
Every eye in the department
is on your place.

607
00:33:28.047 --> 00:33:29.799
Thanks. Detectives.

608
00:33:29.965 --> 00:33:32.302
This is probably
a big inconvenience for you.

609
00:33:32.468 --> 00:33:36.139
No. we're just doing our jobs.
nothing more.

610
00:33:39.499 --> 00:33:42.062
Anyone want some room service?

611
00:33:42.228 --> 00:33:43.728
I'm not really hungry.

612
00:33:43.853 --> 00:33:44.773
Uh...

613
00:33:44.939 --> 00:33:46.648
How about some tea...

614
00:33:46.773 --> 00:33:47.692
Chamomile?

615
00:33:47.858 --> 00:33:50.070
It's nice and relaxing...

616
00:33:50.236 --> 00:33:51.738
Sure.

617
00:33:54.824 --> 00:33:57.327
Nature's full
of powerful concoctions.

618
00:34:00.538 --> 00:34:03.291
I'm gonna make yours a double.

619
00:34:03.457 --> 00:34:08.227
There's gotta be a coffeemaker
around here somewhere.

620
00:34:10.506 --> 00:34:13.009
- I know what you are.
- I'm an attorney.

621
00:34:13.175 --> 00:34:14.177
You're a Hexenbiest.

622
00:34:14.343 --> 00:34:16.179
just like Serena and Camilla.

623
00:34:16.345 --> 00:34:17.347
I saw their marks.

624
00:34:17.513 --> 00:34:18.890
Detective. I don't know what...

625
00:34:19.056 --> 00:34:20.448
You tried to kill
my aunt in the hospital.

626
00:34:20.573 --> 00:34:22.811
but you got me instead.

627
00:34:22.977 --> 00:34:25.397
So were they in on it with you...

628
00:34:25.563 --> 00:34:27.816
Your sisters?

629
00:34:27.982 --> 00:34:30.568
Who do you work for?

630
00:34:35.739 --> 00:34:38.300
Okay.

631
00:34:38.425 --> 00:34:41.369
So you wanna play the victim.

632
00:34:41.494 --> 00:34:44.739
So. tell me...

633
00:34:44.864 --> 00:34:47.209
Why do the mellifers want you dead?

634
00:34:47.376 --> 00:34:49.713
You're a Detective.
Figure it out.

635
00:34:49.879 --> 00:34:51.840
I don't like this
any more than you do.

636
00:34:52.006 --> 00:34:54.134
But if it's my duty to protect you.

637
00:34:54.300 --> 00:34:55.510
I damn well better
have a good reason.

638
00:34:55.676 --> 00:35:00.138
or I might have a bad day at work.

639
00:35:00.263 --> 00:35:02.090
You shouldn't have involved me.

640
00:35:02.215 --> 00:35:04.644
I'm clean.
I have nothing to do with this.

641
00:35:04.810 --> 00:35:07.188
You have just as much
to lose as we do.

642
00:35:07.354 --> 00:35:10.734
I don't wanna go to jail.

643
00:35:10.900 --> 00:35:14.237
How can someone like you
take care of someone like us?

644
00:35:19.165 --> 00:35:22.010
They're going to find you.

645
00:35:22.135 --> 00:35:23.663
Not before I get to her.

646
00:35:23.829 --> 00:35:25.707
There's no guarantee he'll
understand what you've done.

647
00:35:25.873 --> 00:35:30.044
When she's dead. he'll understand.

648
00:35:31.611 --> 00:35:35.383
Let's just get this over with.

649
00:35:37.450 --> 00:35:39.179
They'll find her.

650
00:36:09.375 --> 00:36:11.393
I can't help you unless you tell me

651
00:36:11.518 --> 00:36:13.254
why Melissa Wincroft
wants to kill you.

652
00:36:13.420 --> 00:36:17.342
You have no idea
what you're in the middle of.

653
00:36:17.508 --> 00:36:20.034
Oh. well. then who could
blame me for making a mistake

654
00:36:20.159 --> 00:36:22.472
and letting a queen mellifer
kill another Hexenbiest?

655
00:36:27.016 --> 00:36:28.436
This won't end well.

656
00:36:28.602 --> 00:36:29.938
For you.

657
00:36:30.104 --> 00:36:32.607
Or you.

658
00:36:32.773 --> 00:36:33.848
If something happens to me.

659
00:36:33.973 --> 00:36:37.435
it won't just be a Grimm
killing a Hexenbiest.

660
00:36:37.560 --> 00:36:39.888
It'll be a cop who's let

661
00:36:40.013 --> 00:36:43.535
an innocent woman die on his watch.

662
00:36:43.701 --> 00:36:47.038
Up to you.

663
00:36:47.204 --> 00:36:50.124
Can I get a little help in here?

664
00:36:58.924 --> 00:37:00.176
Won't budge.

665
00:37:08.434 --> 00:37:11.437
It's like they're coming after us!

666
00:37:11.603 --> 00:37:13.857
Oh!

667
00:37:18.051 --> 00:37:19.529
Where are they going?

668
00:37:22.364 --> 00:37:24.409
Adalind.

669
00:37:24.575 --> 00:37:26.160
Adalind?

670
00:37:35.521 --> 00:37:37.043
No sign of force entry.

671
00:37:38.269 --> 00:37:39.389
Why would she run?

672
00:37:39.514 --> 00:37:41.651
- Button's still lit. She didn't take it.
- I'll going up.

673
00:37:43.969 --> 00:37:45.689
Adalind!

674
00:38:03.911 --> 00:38:04.912
Adalind!

675
00:38:21.487 --> 00:38:22.488
Adalind?

676
00:38:30.460 --> 00:38:32.477
I have to kill him.
you don't understand.

677
00:38:32.893 --> 00:38:36.606
Robin. I'm arresting you for the murders
of Serena Dunbrook and Camilla Gotleib.

678
00:38:36.772 --> 00:38:38.274
I did it to protect you.

679
00:38:38.440 --> 00:38:39.343
There's no excuse.

680
00:38:39.468 --> 00:38:42.305
We're clarions.
We send warning calls.

681
00:38:43.382 --> 00:38:44.405
We're under a side.

682
00:38:45.357 --> 00:38:46.491
The lawsuit.

683
00:38:46.657 --> 00:38:49.535
It was conspiracy to get rid of us.
they're not just lawyers.

684
00:38:49.701 --> 00:38:51.329
It doesn't matter.
you killed two people.

685
00:38:51.495 --> 00:38:53.039
Two Hexenbiests.

686
00:38:53.420 --> 00:38:54.791
Closing the mill
was their way

687
00:38:54.957 --> 00:38:56.626
of stopping us
from warning you.

688
00:38:56.792 --> 00:38:57.543
Warning me?

689
00:38:58.598 --> 00:38:59.837
Something's coming.

690
00:39:00.003 --> 00:39:01.493
Something... bad.

691
00:39:02.359 --> 00:39:04.240
I have to finish this.

692
00:39:04.619 --> 00:39:05.647
Melissa.

693
00:39:05.772 --> 00:39:06.427
Don't!

694
00:39:09.077 --> 00:39:09.997
Melissa.

695
00:39:32.828 --> 00:39:35.239
This isn't your problem.
Don't make a mistake.

696
00:39:35.364 --> 00:39:36.332
She'll harm you.
Don't listen to her!

697
00:39:36.499 --> 00:39:38.459
You're a cop!
Do your job!

698
00:39:38.584 --> 00:39:39.752
Melissa!

699
00:39:39.918 --> 00:39:44.072
You're a Grimm!
That's more important!

700
00:39:53.382 --> 00:39:55.226
Help me. Please.

701
00:39:55.392 --> 00:39:57.228
She killed my friends!

702
00:39:57.394 --> 00:40:00.314
Melissa. back away!

703
00:40:02.316 --> 00:40:05.760
Adalind. are you okay?

704
00:40:13.953 --> 00:40:15.580
He's coming for you.

705
00:40:15.746 --> 00:40:17.457
Who?

706
00:40:17.623 --> 00:40:21.794
Beware. It's close.

707
00:40:53.659 --> 00:40:57.355
You have to hunt down the bad ones.

708
00:40:57.480 --> 00:40:58.956
just like your ancestors did.

709
00:41:10.551 --> 00:41:12.804
Hank said you did the right thing.

710
00:41:13.028 --> 00:41:18.109
Sometimes it's not that simple.

711
00:41:18.234 --> 00:41:20.812
If it was simple.
they wouldn't need you.

712
00:41:20.978 --> 00:41:23.398
I don't think I made any difference.

713
00:41:23.564 --> 00:41:26.401
I tried to stop it.

714
00:41:26.567 --> 00:41:28.528
But I didn't.

715
00:41:28.744 --> 00:41:32.823
I think you made
a pretty big difference to Hank

716
00:41:32.948 --> 00:41:34.742
and the woman whose life you saved.

717
00:41:37.086 --> 00:41:38.729
Doesn't that make you feel

718
00:41:38.854 --> 00:41:40.706
a little bit better
about what happened?

719
00:41:45.461 --> 00:41:47.796
Yeah. it does.

720
00:41:54.470 --> 00:41:56.514
I'm cold.

721
00:41:56.680 --> 00:41:59.350
- I'm gonna close the window.
- No. I got it.

722
00:41:59.475 --> 00:42:01.893
- Okay.
- Go back to bed.

723
00:42:23.966 --> 00:42:25.292
Aah!

724
00:42:25.417 --> 00:42:26.977
What happened?

725
00:42:27.102 --> 00:42:29.270
I just got stung.

726
00:42:33.875 --> 00:42:38.556
